    "enDesc": "Admat Kodesh (“Holy Ground”) is an 18th-century work of responsa and insights on the four sections of the Shulchan Arukh. Authored by Rabbi Nissiam Chaim Moshe Mizrachi, the Sephardi chief rabbi of Jerusalem (known as the Rishon LeTzion), the work was published in two sections, the second posthumously. ",
